    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1896-11-12T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1896-11-12T00:00:00-05:00" n="686"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d686">
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Mr. <persName type="from">Springer</persName> to Mr. <persName
                            type="to">Rockhill</persName>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">United States Consulate-General</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Habana</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1896-11-12">
                            <hi rend="italic">November 12, 1896</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                    <seg rendition="#left">No. 211.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <p>
                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Sir</hi>: I have been informed by the sister of Laborde,
                    one of the <hi rend="italic">Competitor</hi> prisoners, that he was yesterday
                    afternoon, at the time of her weekly visit to him, seized with cerebral
                    congestion and removed to the old military hospital of this city.</p>
                <p>Charles Leavitt, another of the prisoners, was removed several days ago to the
                    same hospital, supposed to be ill with yellow fever, but it seems to be a sort
                    of prison fever, induced by confinement and insufficient food.</p>
                <p>Ona Melton, it is stated, is greatly reduced for the same reasons.</p>
                <p>I am, etc.,</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">J. A. Springer.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
